{
  "texts": [
    "In almost all cases, the equivalent width of the Fe Kα line is much larger for these lensed quasars than it is for comparable, non-lensed AGN.",
    "This indicates substantial microlensing and suggests a compact size for that region, comparable to or even smaller than the X-ray continuum region (i.e. the corona, e.g.",
    "Chartas et al. (2017) apply their g-distribution method to the Fe lines seen in RX J1131-1231, QJ 0158-4325, and SDSS J1004+4112.",
    "In this method, the observed Fe line shifts are due to microlensing caustics near the inner edge of the disc, and the distribution of the shifts can provide estimates of the size of the innermost stable circular orbit (ISCO), spin, and inclination (i, with zero being perpendicular to the line-of-sight) of the disc.",
    "To date, results have only been obtained on RX J1131-1231, for which Chartas et al. (2017) report values of r ISCO 8.5r g and i 55 •."
  ]
}